<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={9.66}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={9.66}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={9.66}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={9.66}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>30</li><li>75</li><li>75</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}^{{2}}={9.66}^{{2}}+{9.66}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({9.66}\right)}{\left({9.66}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25}={93.3156}+{93.3156}-{186.6312}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{161.6312}=-{186.6312}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.86604597730712}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={29.997642363958}={30}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({29.997642363958}\right)}}}}{{5.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{9.66}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.9095743999807}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{1.9095743999807}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={75.001178818007}\approx{75}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{29.997642363958}+{75.001178818007}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={75.001178818007}\approx{75}</m></p>

</solution>
